The ISS project!

Im going to be creating a ISS sized space station in LKO. It will be the same layout (as close as i can make it anyway) and have similar modules as well. I will be using stuff from the soviet pack, Hex truss and Metal Wasp Industries Solar Panel pack. To build it I will be using the Proton from the soviet pack and the CSS

When complete it will be around 200 parts, which from the size of it isn't that bad

Stuff i will not be using that is on the ISS:

Dextre or any other robotic arm apart from Canadarm2

Nice looking airlock

Nice looking Cupola

Nice looking radiators

Useful Pirs and rassvet modules, Poisk has been replaced with a docking adapter for my X-37 replica

I would use some really nice stuff from FusTek pack but due to ram limits (i can only use 32 bit so the CSS will work (firespitter issues i guess))

I will start as soon as i am done with Mir.

Edited August 1, 2014 by montyben101

I will increase the distance between the main solar panels in the final version

Criticism is welcome XD (i know the solar panels are too long but i cant find any other ones that are the correct size)

For the truss sturcture it wont be exactly the same. I have not included the S/P 5 trusses and instead added a truss between the S0 truss and the radiator truss. This is to add extra room between the main solar panels and the actual station. Just made this:

As you can see i have not followed the same naming as the ISS and just done it in order to make it easier and less confusing

A link to make it bigger:http://oi58.tinypic.com/15wl5rm.jpg

It looks EXCELLENT! Though I do have a few points:

1. It looks like you made Destiny a bit too short.

2. It seems that you made Node 2 (I'm too bored to look up it's name) too long.

3. You forgot the Z Truss on top of Unity. (The reaction wheels thing).

4. I don't see the external experiments section on Kibo. (Will you make it so you can launch CubeSats from it? Perhaps the KSP Community CubeSat? )

5. I don't see any Russian-US docking port adapters.

Edited August 1, 2014 by Nicholander

Made destiny longer and made node 2 shorter, I think i got them confused or something

I have added a rather crude Z truss with KAS container (a very big one) and reaction wheels

Added external experiments (looks crap im afraid but i will edit it later) with the mini docking port so i can launch CubeSats!, i will look into the community one

The docking adapters will take some time so i will get back to you on that. If they are too difficult i might leave them out.

I will add launch clamps and take some more pics as soon as i have done it all

Oh and i will talk to Romfarer about the robotic arm but its very unlikely. I might make one myself with infernal robotics but iv been having issues with tweak scale not working at all

Im also going to make an ATV and maybe the japanese H-II Transfer Vehicle

Thats Mir, Priorda is yet to be added Its from the soviet pack which also has buran. (though im not using it)

Update: Just added priorda, ISS construction will begin soon
